dc_title_s: Geologic map of the Cupertino and San Jose West quadrangles, Santa Clara and Santa Cruz counties, California
dc_description_s: by Thomas W. Dibblee, Jr. ; edited by John A. Minch. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. "Cupertino quadrangle contour interval 40 feet: Supplementary contour interval 10 feet." "San Jose West quadrangle contour interval 5 feet." "Faculty and Field Geology Students Honorary Map, San Jose State University." "Topographic base map from available USGS 7.5-minute quadrangle. Palo Alto, CA 1997. NIMA 1558 I NW - series V895. Mountain View, CA 1967. DMA 1658 I NE - series V895." "First printing, October 2007." Includes quadrangle location map, index to adjacent 7.5 minute quadrangles, and index to sources of geology, most recent 1974. Includes "pertinent references", most recent 1974.
dc_publisher_s: Santa Barbara Museum of Natural History
